  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">Why is the program called iXperience?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>iXperience is about more than an education. It’s about an all-encompassing summer experience.  A typical day may feature hiking, surfing, yoga or a myriad of other exciting activities. Plus, you will be immersed in a new culture and a beautiful new city.  iXperience is not just a chance to study abroad; it’s the summer of a lifetime.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">Why Cape Town?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>Recently voted the <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2014/01/10/travel/2014-places-to-go.html?_r=0" target="_blank">#1 City to Visit in 2014</a> by the New York Times and named the 2014 World Design Capital, Cape Town is the perfect place for students to learn and explore at the same time. The natural beauty, diverse culture, incredible food and unparalleled opportunities for adventure in ‘The Mother City’ make for a summer experience unlike any other.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">What do I get for my money?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>The course fee includes four weeks of tuition during which time you will be taught by a head instructor and two teaching assistants. On top of this you get accommodation, gourmet breakfast from Monday to Friday, and four iXperience weekend excursions. You will only have to cover airfare, lunch, dinner, and any extra excursions or social outings that you plan independently of the program.</p>

