  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">How competitive is this program?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>iXperience is a very competitive program, as we strive to maintain small class sizes and an intense level of academic rigor. Due to the popularity of the program and the number of applications we receive, our screening process is highly selective and accepts only the best and brightest students from universities around the world.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">What kinds of students are you looking for?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>We are looking for talented, motivated students who are passionate about learning. The key characteristic of successful iX applicants isn't their skill, but rather their attitude. Our strongest applicants demonstrate creative problem solving ability, a genuine and compelling desire to learn, and a strong work ethic.</p>
    <p>
      <b><%= link_to 'Click here', 'http://blog.ixperience.co.za/what-we-look-for-in-applicants/', target: 'blank' %> to learn 3 must-know tips before you begin your iXperience application.</b>
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">How can I contact iX alumni to ask more questions?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>We have an extensive network of over 200 students from schools across the United States and several other countries who are ready and eager to answer any questions you may have.</p>
    <p>
      <%= link_to alumni_path do %>
        <span class="btn btn-primary margin-top margin-bottom">
          Click here to find iX alumni at your school
        </span>
      <% end %>
    </p>
    <p>We've told our alumni that prospective students may be reaching out, so feel free to send them an email! You can reach out to us using the chat bubble on the bottom right of this page—we can also help put you in touch with the alumni best placed to answer your questions.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="accordion-toggle accordion-heading">Do I need a visa to come to South Africa for iXperience?</h3>
  <div class="accordion-inner faq-border">
    <p>It is not necessary for <b>US Citizens</b> and <b>UK Citizens</b> to apply for a visa to come to South Africa for iXperience. If you're a national of one of these counties, you can stay in South Africa for up to 90 days without a visa.</p>
    <p>If you aren't a US or UK citizen, please <%= link_to 'click here','http://www.visasouthafrica.org/visa/who-requires-a-visa/', target: 'blank' %> to visit the Visa South Africa website and check your country’s visa exemption status.</p>
    <p>If you have concerns or questions about visas, please email us at hello@ixperience.co.za or by using the chat bubble on the bottom right of this page. We’re always happy to help.</p>
  </div>

